-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Savola Group, Aldar Properties
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2011-12-27T15:46:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/persian-gulf-stocks-savola-group-aldar-properties.html
Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share
Index  dropped 0.2 percent to 6,400.10 at the 3:30 p.m. close in
Riyadh. Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)   fell 0.8 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols follow company names.  Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)   dropped to the lowest
since April 2005, losing 2.4 percent to 81 fils. The Abu Dhabi-
based property developer said it will complete the conversion of
bonds held by state-owned Mubadala Development Co. into shares
on Jan. 2 and the shares will be listed on the same day.  Savola Group (SAVOLA)   rose 2.9 percent to 28.40 riyals,
the highest since May 4, after the Saudi Arabian food producer
said it was selling land in the kingdom and expanding in Egypt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in  Riyadh  at 
